    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "13. Disconnect oil return hose (turbo charger equipped vehicles)"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582927_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "14. Catalytic converter stay removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582928_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582929_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "15. Oil pan removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582930_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the oil pan mounting bolt (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582931_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Separate the cylinder block from the oil pan using a flat-blade screwdriver or similar tool from the position indicated by the arrow."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Oil pan installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582932_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove old fluid packings, oil, and dirt from oil pan, cylinder block, chain case, bolts, and bolt holes. Remove the adhesive in the O-ring groove of the oil pan."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Install new oil pan packings (A), new O-rings (B), and knock pins (C) in the oil pan."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582933_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Apply Honda Genuine Fluid Packing 1216E to the cylinder block and chain case contact surfaces of the oil pan."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Apply liquid packing with a wire diameter of about 2.5 mm along the dashed line (A).",
        "A liquid packing with a wire diameter of about 6 mm shall be applied to the shaded area (B).",
        "A liquid packing with a wire diameter of about 3 mm shall be applied to the shaded area (C)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582934_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Install the oil pan."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the liquid packing is left on for more than 4 minutes after application, do not install it as it is. Remove the packing once and reapply.",
        "Oil should be injected at least 30 minutes after installation.",
        "Do not touch the liquid packing-applied surface.",
        "Wipe off any fluid packing that protrudes from the crankshaft pulley and drive plate side.",
        "The engine should be started at least 3 hours after installation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582935_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "6",
      "text": "Tighten the oil pan mounting bolts several times in numerical order."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Specified torque",
            "colspan": 2
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "①－⑩:"
          },
          {
            "text": "12N･m (1.2kgf･m)"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "⑪:"
          },
          {
            "text": "44N･m (4.5kgf･m)"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Catalytic Converter Stay Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582936_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582937_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Oil return hose connection (Turbocharger equipped vehicles)"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582938_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Drive Plate Cover Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582939_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Stiffener Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "389_5.0_jpn_11582940_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Tighten the stiffener tightly to the cylinder block, transmission, and oil pan, and temporarily tighten. Tighten several times in numerical order."
    },
